      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For your \"Universal Guide to Sophistication,\" here are some basic rules for professional etiquette and acting sophisticated in a global business setting:\n\n- Address people with titles and last names until explicitly invited to use first names, and be mindful of regional customs that may vary.\n- Dress conservatively and professionally, avoiding overly flashy or revealing clothing, and ensure your attire is clean and pressed.\n- Be punctual and respect other people's time, but also be aware that punctuality can be viewed differently in some cultures.\n- Practice active listening and ask thoughtful questions, but avoid dominating conversations or appearing overly aggressive.\n- Be aware of cultural differences and nuances, and be respectful of local customs, traditions, and values.\n\nRemember, sophistication is not just about following rules, but also about displaying poise, confidence, and a genuine interest in others.",
